<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species might be confused with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schomburgkii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea schomburgkii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of its linear-oblong leaves but both the corolla and sepals are hirsute. From 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pinifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. pinifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is distinguished by the subequal sepals and hirsute corolla and sepals.
</paragraph>
